  <prompt>
    Build the `/help` UI affordance per spec FR-53 — a chat-input-bar control (icon button or
    pill) that triggers the same `CommandHelpPanel` drawer task 081 built. Goal: make Pillar 8
    commands discoverable for users who don't know slash syntax exists.

    Fluent v9 `Button` with help icon, positioned in the chat input bar (likely beside the send
    button). Clicking dispatches to `HardSlashExecutor.executeHardSlash({command: 'help', ...})`
    so the same drawer surface task 081 wired is reused. Tooltip: "Show available commands (/help)".

    ADR-021 binding: dark-mode safe; Fluent v9 semantic tokens only.

    NFR-11 binding: this is purely additive UX; chat input bar still works normally for natural
    language and explicit slashes.

    Frontend-only task; BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Frontend engineer with Fluent v9 + accessibility experience. Comfortable with chat-input-bar
    composition and tooltip surfaces.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `HelpAffordance.tsx` exists; rendered in `ConversationPane.tsx` chat input bar; clicking opens
    the `CommandHelpPanel` drawer (reused from task 081). Dark-mode safe. Accessible
    (`aria-label`, keyboard focus, screen-reader text).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
